   647→     * JSON is a data format and XML is a document format. XML uses elements,
   648→     * attributes, and content text, while JSON uses unordered collections of
   649→     * name/value pairs and arrays of values. JSON does not does not like to
   650→     * distinguish between elements and attributes. Sequences of similar
   651→     * elements are represented as JSONArrays. Content text may be placed in a
   652→     * "content" member. Comments, prologs, DTDs, and <pre>{@code
   653→     * &lt;[ [ ]]>}</pre>
